author: cody

to you that three legged hawk thunders into view\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t pointed nose hung in takeoff mode ready to lift its full passenger load  livery so white, in streaks of blue and red shimmering in heated air, its powerhouse fed howering briefly there, patched underneath shows four great black engines, thrusting power glows  lifting this bird, on pillars of fire clawing at the sky, with strawing desire boiling air on that smooth triangular wing with banshee wail, engines start to sing  quickly pass up into the sky, afterburners on so bright full power soon makes the bird a midget in flight  trailing that wake of black spent might lingering its echoes of concordeâ’s sight  slowly with every second the barrier comes near snug inside her warm interior, passengers have no fear on the ground a double bang, to herald speed so fast inside a dial or two, to show mach 1 is past  the great white bird, built for speed well before her time no other will match her beauty, for grace and line to race the sun to beat the clock, a price we have to pay so expensive to build and run, these last few day  shuffling fast between capitals of state costly time is saved in business small and great the great power of concordeâ’s strength, we hope will never pass new generations will build concordeâ’s son when fatherâ’s out to grass  in countryside pheasant shout, into the clear blue air feeling with their inner sense, vibrations everywhere a minute later, we all hear a double boom around echoing in the evening sky, and stopping the pheasant sound  from the west, a white shaft streaks on high raise your eyes, and see that arrowhead in the sky leaving sound speed, engines slowing down no longer shriek down into warmer atmosphere, concorde guides so sleek  thousands of leagues are left
